  "text": "We use a 70 scope (in preference to a 30 scope) for the procedure as it offers superior visualization of the anterior neck of the scapula. Furthermore, the advantage of viewing around ''acute angles'' with a 70 scope obviates the need for additional portals and thereby eliminates the problem of instrument crowding. [CITATION_1] The technique comprises four steps, all performed arthroscopically, in addition to the Bankart repair. Step 1: coracoid preparation, drilling, and osteotomy",
  "correct_citation": {
